  "name": "Matthew 19:1–15",
  "localizedName": "Matthew 19:1–15",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Pharisees were looking for ways to trap Jesus. They asked a question about "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108514",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "divorce"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". The Law of Moses allowed people to get divorced. So they thought that God approved of divorce."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "But Jesus taught them what God wanted for the world when he created it. Two people are made one when they get "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108206",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "married"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". God wants them to always stay as one. They are like a picture of God’s faithful love. God helps some people to stay single. The important thing is to serve the kingdom of heaven whether married or single."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then Jesus welcomed some children that his disciples were trying to send away. The children weren’t like the Pharisees who tried to trick Jesus. They simply trusted Jesus and received his blessing. He talked about them to explain the kingdom of heaven. His kingdom is for people who are humble and trust Jesus completely."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
